# BFS (Level Order Traversal) Quick Revision Notes

---

# What is BFS?

BFS (Breadth First Search) visits nodes level by level.

```text
Level 0 → Level 1 → Level 2 → Level 3 ...
```

Unlike DFS, BFS explores all nodes at the current depth before moving deeper.

---

# Core Idea

```text
Visit Neighbors First
```

or

```text
Process Tree Level by Level
```

---

# Data Structure Used

```java
Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();
```

### Why Queue?

Because Queue follows:

```text
FIFO
(First In First Out)
```

which naturally processes nodes level-wise.

---

# BFS Template (Must Memorize)

```java
public List<List<Integer>> levelOrder(TreeNode root) {

    List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();

    if(root == null)
        return result;

    Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();
    queue.offer(root);

    while(!queue.isEmpty()) {

        int size = queue.size();

        List<Integer> level = new ArrayList<>();

        for(int i = 0; i < size; i++) {

            TreeNode current = queue.poll();

            level.add(current.val);

            if(current.left != null)
                queue.offer(current.left);

            if(current.right != null)
                queue.offer(current.right);
        }

        result.add(level);
    }

    return result;
}
```

