# Most Important Observation

```text
Queue Size = Number of Nodes in Current Level
```

This single trick solves most BFS questions.

---

# BFS Interview Tricks

---

## Trick 1

Store:

```java
int size = queue.size();
```

before loop.

Reason:

```text
size = nodes present in current level
```

Used in:

- Level Order Traversal
- Zigzag Traversal
- Right Side View
- Average of Levels
- Level Sum

---

## Trick 2

Never do:

```java
for(int i = 0; i < queue.size(); i++)
```

because queue size changes dynamically.

Always:

```java
int size = queue.size();

for(int i = 0; i < size; i++)
```

---

## Trick 3

BFS = Shortest Path in Unweighted Graph

Whenever question says:

```text
Minimum Steps
Minimum Moves
Shortest Distance
Shortest Transformation
```

Think:

```text
BFS
```

---

## Trick 4

Level Number Tracking

```java
int level = 0;

while(!queue.isEmpty()) {

    int size = queue.size();

    // process level

    level++;
}
```

Used for:

- Maximum Depth
- Minimum Depth
- Distance Problems

---

## Trick 5

Multi-Source BFS

Push multiple starting nodes.

```java
queue.offer(node1);
queue.offer(node2);
queue.offer(node3);
```

Used in:

- Rotten Oranges
- Walls and Gates
- Fire Spread
- Virus Spread

